<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Mastermind Game</title>
    <link href= "<%=url('/styles.css')%>" type="text/css" rel = "stylesheet"/>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Caveat&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  </head>

  <body class ='index'>
    <div class = 'rules-container'>
      <h2>Rules</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Your mission is to guess the code generated by the computer in <div class= 'important'>12</div> turns or less</li>
        <li>Each turn you try to guess the code</li>
        <li>Based on your guess the computer will provide feedback on how close you were to correctly guessing the code</li>
        <li>The computer feedback will be of two types
        <ul>
          <li><div class='important'>Exact matches:</div> You guessed the right color at the right position.</li>
          <li><div class ='important'>Color Match:</div> You guessed the right color but it was at the wrong position</li>
        </ul></li>
      </ol>
    </div>
    <form action='/play'>
      <input type='submit' value="Let's Play">
    </form>
  </body>
</html>